Backport of upstream paramiko fix for CVE-2023-48795 (Terrapin attack).

Implements the SSH "strict kex" mode (kex-strict-{c,s}-v00@openssh.com)
together with sequence-number reset on NEWKEYS, MessageOrderError on
out-of-order pre-NEWKEYS packets, and a hard error on sequence-number
rollover during the initial key exchange.

Adapted from upstream paramiko commits:
  773a174 - Basic strict-kex-mode agreement mechanics
  75e311d - Enforce zero seqno on kexinit
  f4dedac - Raise new exception type when unexpected messages appear
  fa46de7 - Reset sequence numbers on rekey
  96db1e2 - Raise exception when sequence numbers rollover during initial kex
  33508c9 - Expand MessageOrderError use to handle more packet types

Backported for paramiko 2.8.1 (pypi). Test files from upstream are not
included because the upstream regression tests rely on a pytest-style
server() helper, BadSeqPacketizer fixture and tests/_util.py extensions
that do not exist in 2.8.1's unittest-based test harness; backporting
them would require backporting the entire test infrastructure.

